down South
Homonym Number:
Word Class:adverb
Sense Number:
Definition:in modern usage applied to any place considerably to the south of the speaker, esp. the south of the South Island. Contrast up North.
Origin:[none]
Register:
Register 2:
Domain:[none]
Region:[none]
